>jd: ?EINRWY B2 WE. +18 326
#note this at least I believe is a good play - even though I empty the bag, I also set up an unblockable spot. there are not many spots for her to score at. or so I thought. quackle actually sems to agree, saying that I win 42% of the time (a.k.a. 15/36). that's not so bad. but then again, I don't really trust quackle to do that sort of math correctly. the other play that does well, elfin at 9A, I think does so because it blocks ENCODE (which I did not spot at the time).
>Odette_Rio: CEGINRS 3A R.. +3 332
